TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(2,20,1);
$b=random(2,20,1);
$c=random(2,20,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Use the Laws of logarithms to rewrite the expression
\[
\log\left(\frac{x^{$a} y^{$b}}{z^{$c}}\right)
\]
in a form with no logarithm of a product, quotient or power.
$BR
After rewriting we have
\[
\log\left(\frac{x^{$a} y^{$b}}{z^{$c}}\right)= A \log(x) + B \log(y)+ C \log(z)
\]
$BR
with
$BR
\(A=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR

\(B=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
and
$BR
\(C=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = $a;
$ans2 = $b;
$ans3 = -$c;

ANS(std_num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(std_num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(std_num_cmp($ans3));

